    p.-text
      | Web pages do not contain anything that flashes more than three times in any one second period, or the flash is below the general flash and red flash thresholds.
    ul.-text
      li 
        i.chi-icon.-xs.-icon--primary.icon-checkbox-checked.-mr--1
        | Do users have access to the full content of a site without inducing seizures due to photosensitivity?
      li 
        i.chi-icon.-xs.-icon--primary.icon-checkbox-checked.-mr--1
        | Can the user suppress any flashing content before it begins?
      li 
        i.chi-icon.-xs.-icon--primary.icon-checkbox-checked.-mr--1
        | If there is a flashing area, is it a small area (less then 25% of 10 degrees of the visual field - representing the central area of vision in the eye - approximately 341 x 256 pixels)?
      li 
        i.chi-icon.-xs.-icon--primary.icon-checkbox-checked.-mr--1
        | Is the flashing limited on only 3 times in any one second period?
